.TH "thermal_emergency_poweroff" 9 "thermal_emergency_poweroff" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
thermal_emergency_poweroff \- Trigger an emergency system poweroff
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" thermal_emergency_poweroff
.BI "(void "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "void" 12
no arguments
.SH "DESCRIPTION"

This may be called from any critical situation to trigger a system shutdown
after a known period of time. By default this is not scheduled.
